Left ICA and CCA angiograms were performed for emergency endovascular treatment of
acute ischemic stroke.
Under supine position, sterilization with alcohol at both inguinal areas and aseptic
draping were done. After local anesthesia with 1% lidocaine, right femoral arterial
puncture (Sono guided) was performed using Seldinger's method. SF Long Sheath, 5F
Headhunter angiocatheter, Phenom 21 microcatheter, 035 Terumo guidewire, Traxcess
microwire, React 071 were used.
Puncture site was sealed with Perclose device.
The patient tolerated well without specific procedure-related complications.
Ix: Lt M1 occlusion on CTA, initial NIHSS score 21.
Procedure for Lt M1 occlusion:
- 8F Long Sheath was placed at right femoral artery with coaxial technique.
- Left ICA angiogram revealed occlusion of Lt M1.
- Phenom 21 microcatheter was navigated beyond the occlusion site using microwire.
- React 071 was navigated to the occluded segment.
- After about 3 minutes, [React 071] was retrieved and suction thrombectomy was
performed simultaneously.
- A large clot was extracted through [React 071] device.
- Control angiogram showed TICI 3 recanalized status.
All devices were retrieved and the puncture site was sealed with Perclose device.
Impression:
Successful recanalization of Lt M1 occlusion.
Mild stenosis of Lt cervical ICA was noted.
Additionally, ulceration was found in Lt cervical ICA.

Left ICA and CCA angiograms were performed for emergency endovascular treatment of acute ischemic stroke .

Under supine position , sterilization with alcohol at both inguinal areas and aseptic draping were done . After local anesthesia with 1 % lidocaine , right femoral arterial
puncture ( Sono guided ) was performed using Seldinger's method . SF Long Sheath , 5F Headhunter angiocatheter , Phenom 21 microcatheter , 035 Terumo guidewire , Traxcess microwire , React 071 were used .
Puncture site was sealed with Perclose device .
The patient tolerated well without specific procedure - related complications .
Ix : Lt M1 occlusion on CTA , initial NIHSS score 21 .

- 8F Long Sheath was placed at right femoral artery with coaxial technique .
- Left ICA angiogram revealed occlusion of Lt M1 .
- Phenom 21 microcatheter was navigated beyond the occlusion site using microwire .
- React 071 was navigated to the occluded segment .
- After about 3 minutes , [ React 071 ] was retrieved and suction thrombectomy was performed simultaneously .
- A large clot was extracted through [ React 071 ] device .
- Control angiogram showed TICI 3 recanalized status .
All devices were retrieved and the puncture site was sealed with Perclose device .

Successful recanalization of Lt M1 occlusion .
Mild stenosis of Lt cervical ICA was noted .
Additionally , ulceration was found in Lt cervical ICA .
